  },
  {
    "uid": "doi:10.2139/ssrn.7068293",
    "drop": false,
    "field": "management",
    "role": "agent",
    "bullets": [
      "Simulated e-commerce fulfillment warehouse with rapid order growth and changing assortments, where two decision agents interact in an event-driven environment and are evaluated jointly in an integrated warehouse simulation.",
      "Two reinforcement learning agents, no language model named, handle zone slotting and replenishment; Action-Linked Credit Assignment links each order to its resulting inventory state, evaluated against rule-based baselines rather than a labelled benchmark.",
      "The framework achieves over ten times the cumulative reward of rule-based baselines, cutting replenishment orders by 19 percent and stockout ratios by 35 percent, with stable performance when new products are introduced."
    ],
